319
00:18:22.580 --> 00:18:26.500
Thank you to the section chairs and AACR for the opportunity to present

320
00:18:26.560 --> 00:18:30.340
my work today. My name is Yue Xu from the Baylor College of Medicine.

321
00:18:32.140 --> 00:18:35.659
This work I will be sharing introduces a tumor-targeted ionizable lipid

322
00:18:35.740 --> 00:18:37.060
nanoparticles platform

323
00:18:37.980 --> 00:18:41.540
that delivers IL-12 circRNA for lung cancer

324
00:18:41.600 --> 00:18:45.460
immunotherapy. This study was carried out at the University of Toronto

325
00:18:46.160 --> 00:18:49.040
and published in "Advanced Materials" in 2024.

326
00:18:50.280 --> 00:18:51.180
And this slide,

327
00:18:52.180 --> 00:18:55.740
listing my disclosures. I have no relevant financial

328
00:18:55.780 --> 00:18:57.100
relationships to disclose.

329
00:18:58.340 --> 00:19:02.200
Let me start with the rationale for using circRNA

330
00:19:02.240 --> 00:19:06.220
as a therapeutic modality. Over the past five years,

331
00:19:06.480 --> 00:19:08.080
linear mRNA has transformed the

332
00:19:09.280 --> 00:19:12.860
vaccine development and opened the door to a broad

333
00:19:12.980 --> 00:19:16.920
class of RNA therapeutics. But when we move from SARS-CoV

334
00:19:17.120 --> 00:19:19.619
vaccine into oncology, the requirements

335
00:19:20.560 --> 00:19:24.440
change a lot. For tumor immunotherapy, we need sustained local protein

336
00:19:24.460 --> 00:19:24.960
expression.

337
00:19:26.420 --> 00:19:29.720
Linear mRNA has three fundamental limitations that makes

338
00:19:30.220 --> 00:19:34.180
this difficult. It's unstable and short-lived expression and require

339
00:19:34.240 --> 00:19:38.020
extra chemical modification like 5-prime capping to

340
00:19:38.100 --> 00:19:40.580
avoid the innate immune sensing.

341
00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:44.760
circRNA offers a way around each of these,

342
00:19:44.860 --> 00:19:48.040
because both ends of the molecule are covalently joined.

343
00:19:48.280 --> 00:19:52.240
It is resistant to enzyme degradation, and

344
00:19:52.320 --> 00:19:55.520
this translates into three practical advantages that are

345
00:19:55.620 --> 00:19:58.020
directly relevant to cancer therapy.

346
00:19:58.240 --> 00:20:00.080
First thing is the persistent

347
00:20:01.240 --> 00:20:05.100
protein expression in vivo. The second thing is robust thermal stability, and the

348
00:20:05.120 --> 00:20:07.420
third thing is a simple manufacturing process.

349
00:20:07.800 --> 00:20:11.769
No 5-prime capping, no 3-prime tearing, and

350
00:20:11.919 --> 00:20:15.300
no need for extra chemical modification.

351
00:20:15.400 --> 00:20:18.829
Together, these features support better efficacy, a

352
00:20:18.940 --> 00:20:22.860
potentially improved safety profile, lower cost of goods,

353
00:20:22.940 --> 00:20:26.380
and easier logistics. So conceptually,

354
00:20:26.540 --> 00:20:30.040
circRNA is a well-matched cargo for cytokine-based immunotherapy,

355
00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:34.680
where we want durable localized expression at the tumor site.

356
00:20:37.440 --> 00:20:40.420
So the question is, why we choose IL-12 as our cargo?

357
00:20:40.820 --> 00:20:44.730
The payload we choose is IL-12. IL-12 is a cytokine

358
00:20:44.800 --> 00:20:47.560
composed of p35 and p40

359
00:20:48.120 --> 00:20:50.380
subunit, and it is the most potent

360
00:20:51.860 --> 00:20:54.209
pro-inflammatory cytokine in cancer immunotherapy.

361
00:20:54.700 --> 00:20:57.760
As shown in the figure, IL-12 acts on

362
00:20:58.640 --> 00:21:01.100
multiple arms of the immune system at the same time.

363
00:21:01.160 --> 00:21:05.000
It activates CD8 T cells and NK cells, drives the

364
00:21:05.080 --> 00:21:08.530
interferon gamma production, promotes Th1 polarization, and

365
00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:12.360
reprograms the myeloid compartment in the tumor

366
00:21:12.420 --> 00:21:16.300
microenvironment. In the preclinical models, recombinant IL-12

367
00:21:16.320 --> 00:21:19.940
has produced some of the most dramatic anti-tumor responses ever

368
00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:23.760
reported. And yet, despite more than two decades of the

369
00:21:23.780 --> 00:21:25.740
clinical efforts, IL-12 has been

370
00:21:26.560 --> 00:21:30.440
successfully translated in the clinical. The reason is well-known.

371
00:21:30.520 --> 00:21:34.400
Systemic recombinant IL-12 is associated with serious toxicity

372
00:21:34.440 --> 00:21:36.920
due to off-target immune activation.

373
00:21:36.980 --> 00:21:38.020
The therapeutic window is

374
00:21:39.020 --> 00:21:42.940
extremely narrow. So the central question of this work

375
00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:46.380
is, can we retain the anti-tumor potency of IL-12 while

376
00:21:46.480 --> 00:21:48.580
confining the effectivity to the tumor?

377
00:21:49.080 --> 00:21:52.120
Our hypothesis is that delivery of the IL-12 in

378
00:21:52.980 --> 00:21:56.760
the form of circRNA encapsulated into a tumor-targeted

379
00:21:57.160 --> 00:22:00.680
ionizable lipid nanoparticle can achieve this therapeutic window.

380
00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:01.740
So

381
00:22:03.020 --> 00:22:04.920
this slide layouts the overall concept.

382
00:22:05.160 --> 00:22:09.120
We encapsulate the IL-12 circRNA into our ionizable lipid

383
00:22:09.160 --> 00:22:11.200
nanoparticle. The lipid nanoparticle is

384
00:22:12.120 --> 00:22:16.000
delivered locally, either by the tumor injection for subcutaneous tumor

385
00:22:16.080 --> 00:22:19.120
or by intratracheal injection for lung tumors.

386
00:22:19.520 --> 00:22:23.000
Once taken up by the cells, the site of the delivery, the circRNA is

387
00:22:23.040 --> 00:22:26.860
translated into functional IL-12, which is secreted in the local

388
00:22:27.160 --> 00:22:31.140
tumor microenvironment. So we have three questions here to answer.

389
00:22:32.220 --> 00:22:35.920
The first question is, can we make pure functional IL-12 circRNA at

390
00:22:36.040 --> 00:22:36.320
scale?

391
00:22:37.340 --> 00:22:41.260
The second question is here, can we identify a lipid nanoparticle formulation

392
00:22:41.300 --> 00:22:44.220
that is optimized for circRNA delivery?

393
00:22:44.260 --> 00:22:47.360
The last question is, does this combination actually work

394
00:22:47.580 --> 00:22:51.020
both as monotherapy and in

395
00:22:51.060 --> 00:22:53.700
combination with immune checkpoint blockade?

396
00:22:54.820 --> 00:22:58.100
So first, we do the

397
00:22:58.520 --> 00:23:02.160
circRNA production. We use the PIE strategy, which allow

398
00:23:02.380 --> 00:23:05.120
self-splicing circulation of an IVT

399
00:23:05.280 --> 00:23:09.160
precursor. The constructor is designed so that

400
00:23:09.320 --> 00:23:12.720
the IVT derives translation of the IL-12

401
00:23:12.760 --> 00:23:16.720
p35 and p40 subunits from the circular format, yielding a

402
00:23:16.780 --> 00:23:20.600
back to p70 format. A critical challenge with

403
00:23:20.620 --> 00:23:24.480
circRNA is purity. The IVT reaction

404
00:23:24.520 --> 00:23:28.440
produce a mixture of circular products, unreacted

405
00:23:28.540 --> 00:23:31.480
linear precursor, and nicked intermediates.

406
00:23:32.120 --> 00:23:34.000
These side products are not inert.

407
00:23:34.380 --> 00:23:38.060
They trigger the innate immune sensing and then compromising the

408
00:23:38.420 --> 00:23:41.940
reproducibility. So we develop a size

409
00:23:42.020 --> 00:23:44.740
exclusion HPLC purification protocol.

410
00:23:44.980 --> 00:23:46.300
As seen in the panel B,

411
00:23:47.280 --> 00:23:51.170
you can see a clean separation of circRNA IL-12 from the

412
00:23:51.260 --> 00:23:54.780
surrounding species. We collected the vials one

413
00:23:55.560 --> 00:23:58.000
through the vials eight across the main peak.

414
00:23:58.470 --> 00:24:01.940
Panel C shows the gel analysis of these fractions.

415
00:24:02.300 --> 00:24:05.860
The lower band is the purified IL-12 circRNA, and the

416
00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:08.968
upside products... were extruded.

417
00:24:09.308 --> 00:24:12.948
This step is what gives us a reproducible cargo to

418
00:24:13.028 --> 00:24:14.348
downstream work.

419
00:24:16.108 --> 00:24:19.988
Secondly, we want to use our delivery system for

420
00:24:20.008 --> 00:24:23.588
this specific RTL of circRNA. CircRNA is chemically

421
00:24:23.628 --> 00:24:27.448
distinct from the linear RNA. It has no 5 prime cap,

422
00:24:27.588 --> 00:24:31.028
no poly-A tail, and therefore different physical properties.

423
00:24:31.408 --> 00:24:35.128
So even nanoparticles optimized for mRNA are not optimal for

424
00:24:35.228 --> 00:24:38.728
circRNA. We therefore build our own ionizable lipid library

425
00:24:39.088 --> 00:24:40.948
specific for the circRNA delivery.

426
00:24:41.548 --> 00:24:45.268
We use the four component reaction called a OB as a

427
00:24:45.308 --> 00:24:47.548
combinatorial chemistry platform.

428
00:24:48.048 --> 00:24:51.878
As shown in this panel, the four building blocks are AMI

429
00:24:51.968 --> 00:24:55.528
group, an isocyanate linker, and two lipid tails

430
00:24:55.568 --> 00:24:58.608
contributed by caprylic acid and an aldehyde.

431
00:24:59.258 --> 00:25:03.128
This gives us the module high throughput methods overnight synthesis at

432
00:25:03.228 --> 00:25:06.487
room temperature in ethanol to generate a chemical diverse lipid

433
00:25:06.528 --> 00:25:07.368
library.

434
00:25:08.188 --> 00:25:11.348
Panel B shows the specific building blocks we used.

435
00:25:12.048 --> 00:25:12.827
Two AMI

436
00:25:13.628 --> 00:25:17.558
head groups, three isocyanate links, four caprylic acid tails, and

437
00:25:17.668 --> 00:25:21.548
four aldehyde tails. Combinatorial assembly give us a

438
00:25:21.628 --> 00:25:24.848
matrix of candidates on ionizable lipids, each of which

439
00:25:26.248 --> 00:25:30.228
we formulate into a four-component lipid nanoparticles, ionizable lipid,

440
00:25:30.628 --> 00:25:33.708
tail lipid, cholesterol, and the PEG lipid 2000.

441
00:25:34.368 --> 00:25:38.088
Encapsulating a FLOC circRNA reporter, we then

442
00:25:38.528 --> 00:25:41.368
screen the entire library in vivo for protein expression.

443
00:25:41.728 --> 00:25:44.068
The heat map on the right summarizes the output.

444
00:25:44.408 --> 00:25:47.248
The top-performing lipid, we name it

445
00:25:47.258 --> 00:25:50.808
H1AL1A1B3, combines the H1 head groups,

446
00:25:51.228 --> 00:25:54.308
the HL1 linker, and the A1 caprylic acid.

447
00:25:54.368 --> 00:25:54.788
And the

448
00:25:57.428 --> 00:26:01.368
B3 aldehyde tails is the formulation we carried forward for

449
00:26:01.468 --> 00:26:02.768
subsequent experiments.

450
00:26:04.448 --> 00:26:08.048
With the lipid nanoparticle in hand, we next ask whether

451
00:26:08.058 --> 00:26:11.648
circRNA actually delivers the kinetic advantage that we

452
00:26:11.728 --> 00:26:15.628
hypothesized. We compared the R12 circRNA

453
00:26:15.668 --> 00:26:19.118
to R12 mRNA, both formulated in the same lipid

454
00:26:19.128 --> 00:26:22.908
nanoparticles. The left two panels show in vitro

455
00:26:22.948 --> 00:26:26.608
kinetics in two lung cancer cell lines, A549 and

456
00:26:26.768 --> 00:26:30.628
HKP1, for R12 mRNA. R12 protein in

457
00:26:30.688 --> 00:26:33.838
the supernatant peaks on day one, and

458
00:26:34.408 --> 00:26:38.388
falls below the detection limit by day three to day

459
00:26:38.468 --> 00:26:41.988
four. In contrast, R12 circRNA maintains R12

460
00:26:42.008 --> 00:26:45.728
concentration about 500 picograms

461
00:26:45.828 --> 00:26:49.288
per milliliter out to day six or seven,

462
00:26:49.728 --> 00:26:52.948
roughly a two-fold expression of the expression window.

463
00:26:53.528 --> 00:26:57.248
The in vivo kinetic on the right panel,

464
00:26:58.168 --> 00:27:02.008
measured by the FLOC bioluminescence after the intramuscular injection

465
00:27:02.048 --> 00:27:05.948
at 48 hours. The FLOC signal from the circRNA group

466
00:27:06.008 --> 00:27:08.668
is significantly higher than from the mRNA group.

467
00:27:09.488 --> 00:27:12.388
So the kinetic benefits of circRNA is real.

468
00:27:12.468 --> 00:27:12.948
It's

469
00:27:14.228 --> 00:27:17.868
reproducible across the system, and it's most important

470
00:27:17.908 --> 00:27:21.528
prominent at the later time points, which is

471
00:27:21.548 --> 00:27:24.748
exactly where it matters for sustained immunotherapy.

472
00:27:26.328 --> 00:27:30.008
So now we move to the efficacy. We first test

473
00:27:30.288 --> 00:27:33.998
the platform in the Lewis lung carcinoma, or

474
00:27:34.128 --> 00:27:38.028
LLC-1, subcutaneous models. The designs shown in the panel

475
00:27:38.128 --> 00:27:42.048
A, mice was incorporated on the day one.

476
00:27:42.118 --> 00:27:46.028
It received a single intra-tumoral dose of five micrograms of

477
00:27:46.068 --> 00:27:49.028
R12 circRNA-lipid nanoparticles on day seven.

478
00:27:49.488 --> 00:27:53.308
An Anti-PD-L1 antibody used the IP injection on day 10 and

479
00:27:53.388 --> 00:27:57.248
the 13th. Panel B shows the tumor growth curves

480
00:27:57.368 --> 00:28:01.268
for the five groups. First group is untreated one, second group

481
00:28:01.328 --> 00:28:05.178
is scrambled circRNA-LNP, and the third one is the R12

482
00:28:05.188 --> 00:28:09.128
circRNA-LNP monotherapy, and the last one is antibody PD-L1

483
00:28:09.168 --> 00:28:10.488
mersibi, and the control.

484
00:28:11.748 --> 00:28:14.048
We use both of them as a combination.

485
00:28:14.508 --> 00:28:16.028
Two points are worth highlighting.

486
00:28:16.108 --> 00:28:19.808
First is the anti-PD-L1 immunotherapy in LLC-1 is

487
00:28:19.888 --> 00:28:23.348
essentially ineffective. The yellow curve tracks almost

488
00:28:23.468 --> 00:28:26.888
identically with untreated and scrambled control, consistent with

489
00:28:26.928 --> 00:28:30.868
the LLC-1 being a well-documented immune code checkpoint resident

490
00:28:30.888 --> 00:28:31.228
model.

491
00:28:32.628 --> 00:28:33.548
And the second

492
00:28:35.208 --> 00:28:38.768
R12 circRNA monotherapy alone produced a robust, durable

493
00:28:38.788 --> 00:28:39.888
tumor

494
00:28:41.168 --> 00:28:45.088
regression. And the combination of the R12 circRNA plus anti-PD-L1

495
00:28:45.108 --> 00:28:48.888
