00:57:25.988 --> 00:57:29.548
models. In these orthotopic models, we did

994
00:57:29.948 --> 00:57:33.888
two intravenous injections of CBD anti-CTLA-4, showing a

995
00:57:33.928 --> 00:57:36.468
significant increase in overall survival of

996
00:57:36.608 --> 00:57:40.568
140% compared to the wild type counterpart and

997
00:57:40.648 --> 00:57:44.508
our PBS control groups. Also showing that the tumor size could be

998
00:57:44.528 --> 00:57:46.588
controlled on day 10 as well.

999
00:57:48.068 --> 00:57:51.828
We also used CBD ipilimumab, a humanized version

1000
00:57:51.948 --> 00:57:53.318
of anti-CTLA-4,

1001
00:57:54.228 --> 00:57:55.028
in our human

1002
00:57:56.628 --> 00:58:00.228
radio-resistant PDX models implanted into PBMC

1003
00:58:00.288 --> 00:58:04.168
humanized mice. And in these experiments, we identified that CBD

1004
00:58:04.188 --> 00:58:07.348
ipilimumab could also extend survival compared to the control,

1005
00:58:08.628 --> 00:58:12.288
and also control the tumor size on day 13.

1006
00:58:13.328 --> 00:58:17.308
So we identified that the CBD anti-CTLA-4 could

1007
00:58:17.348 --> 00:58:20.928
accumulate at greater concentrations or greater within the tumor

1008
00:58:21.288 --> 00:58:25.248
and also extend survival. But what was the immune effects leading to

1009
00:58:25.288 --> 00:58:28.948
this change? So we performed single-cell RNA sequencing on the

1010
00:58:28.988 --> 00:58:32.708
immune cells within the tumor. And in the top panel, you can

1011
00:58:32.788 --> 00:58:36.128
see the sub-clustering analysis of the T cells within the

1012
00:58:36.148 --> 00:58:40.088
tumor. Highlighted in blue are the exhausted T cells, highlighted in red

1013
00:58:40.128 --> 00:58:43.768
are the regulatory T cells. And on the right-hand side, you can see that

1014
00:58:44.228 --> 00:58:47.968
in the CBD treated T cells versus the control, there was almost a

1015
00:58:47.988 --> 00:58:51.688
complete loss of these exhausted T cells that we saw in the

1016
00:58:51.728 --> 00:58:52.388
control group.

1017
00:58:53.348 --> 00:58:57.297
But the Tregs, while still reduced, it was unclear whether or not this

1018
00:58:57.328 --> 00:58:59.237
reduction in Tregs was substantial.

1019
00:58:59.828 --> 00:59:03.748
So we performed flow cytometry experiments to determine

1020
00:59:03.788 --> 00:59:07.568
whether or not regulatory T cells were decreased after CBD CTLA-4

1021
00:59:07.608 --> 00:59:10.048
treatment, and we found that they were intratumorally.

1022
00:59:11.208 --> 00:59:15.168
Additionally, looking at the whole immune cell population within the tumor,

1023
00:59:15.608 --> 00:59:19.008
we also found that dendritic cells in their total

1024
00:59:19.088 --> 00:59:22.848
proportion were increased after CBD CTLA-4

1025
00:59:22.908 --> 00:59:23.308
treatment.

1026
00:59:24.408 --> 00:59:28.108
So we did sub-cluster analysis on these dendritic cells to identify

1027
00:59:28.168 --> 00:59:31.908
what types of dendritic cells were driving this increase in dendritic cell

1028
00:59:31.968 --> 00:59:35.368
change. And when comparing the

1029
00:59:35.408 --> 00:59:39.208
clusters between the CBD group and the control group, we found that

1030
00:59:39.248 --> 00:59:42.228
this change was largely driven by an increase in these

1031
00:59:42.308 --> 00:59:45.608
migratory activated dendritic cells, as well as

1032
00:59:45.668 --> 00:59:49.428
CDC1s, both dendritic cell types known for

1033
00:59:49.508 --> 00:59:51.388
their anti-tumor effects.

1034
00:59:52.668 --> 00:59:56.468
So we identified that the drug could accumulate within the

1035
00:59:56.528 --> 01:00:00.448
GBM tumor, it could extend survival, as well as modify the

1036
01:00:00.488 --> 01:00:03.528
tumor immune system or the tumor immune profile.

1037
01:00:03.648 --> 01:00:06.888
But we wanted to further address the translational

1038
01:00:06.948 --> 01:00:10.688
application of CBD anti-CTLA-4. So

1039
01:00:10.728 --> 01:00:14.268
we used a human glioma slice culture experiment,

1040
01:00:14.968 --> 01:00:18.728
where we took human GBM tissue provided by the UAB Biorepository.

1041
01:00:19.248 --> 01:00:23.118
We created slices of these human GBM tissues with a vibratome,

1042
01:00:23.628 --> 01:00:25.648
and then we cultured them in media

1043
01:00:26.788 --> 01:00:29.908
along with the CBD humanized ipilimumab

1044
01:00:30.648 --> 01:00:34.308
for three days. And then after the three days, we performed flow

1045
01:00:34.348 --> 01:00:37.968
cytometry to assess the changes in the intratumoral Tregs.

1046
01:00:38.388 --> 01:00:41.948
And what we found was that in the group that received the CBD

1047
01:00:41.988 --> 01:00:45.708
ipilimumab treatment, we were able to reduce the intratumoral Tregs,

1048
01:00:46.128 --> 01:00:49.248
showing the translational possibilities of

1049
01:00:49.308 --> 01:00:52.708
CBD in these human GBM slice cultures.

1050
01:00:54.748 --> 01:00:58.608
In all, we identified that collagen I and III, while

1051
01:00:58.668 --> 01:01:01.928
minimally expressed in the normal brain, are strongly

1052
01:01:01.988 --> 01:01:05.848
upregulated in recurrent GBM. And in developing

1053
01:01:06.008 --> 01:01:08.808
a collagen binding anti-CTLA-4 antibody,

1054
01:01:09.608 --> 01:01:13.088
we found that they could selectively accumulate within recurrent GBM

1055
01:01:13.148 --> 01:01:17.076
tumorsThe monotherapy could improve survival in

1056
01:01:17.156 --> 01:01:20.416
recurrent GBM mouse models, whereas the wild type could not.

1057
01:01:21.376 --> 01:01:25.016
And CBD anti-CTLA-4 could decrease intratumoral

1058
01:01:25.036 --> 01:01:28.316
Tregs as well as exhausted dysfunctional T

1059
01:01:28.416 --> 01:01:31.996
cells. Our humanized CBD ipilimumab version

1060
01:01:32.036 --> 01:01:35.956
prolonged survival in PBMC humanized recurrent GBM models

1061
01:01:36.656 --> 01:01:40.556
and could reduce intratumoral Tregs in our ex vivo

1062
01:01:40.776 --> 01:01:42.676
3D human slice cultures.

1063
01:01:43.716 --> 01:01:47.676
So in all, CBD anti-CTLA-4 could be a promising treatment

1064
01:01:47.736 --> 01:01:51.606
for recurrent GBM, and collagen binding technologies can be applied

1065
01:01:51.656 --> 01:01:55.236
to multiple antibodies and potentially revolutionize therapeutic

1066
01:01:55.276 --> 01:01:56.956
strategies for brain tumors.

